8 HOUSE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 282, L.D. 598, “An Act to Require Minimum
9 Pay for Reporting to Work”
10 Amend the bill in section 2 in §639-A in subsection 1 in paragraph A in the last line
11 (page 1, line 13 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "1" the following: 'or an employee
12 of a public employer, as defined in section 626, who is covered by a collective bargaining
13 agreement'
14 Amend the bill in section 2 in §639-A in subsection 1 in paragraph B in the last 2 lines
15 (page 1, lines 16 and 17 in L.D.) by striking out the following: ""Employer" does not
16 include a public employer as defined in section 626."
17 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
18 number to read consecutively.
19 SUMMARY
2200 This amendment removes the provision in the bill that excludes public employers from
2211 the definition of "employer." It adds an exception to the definition of "employee" for an
2222 employee of a public employer who is covered by a collective bargaining agreement.
